 training and inference on Apple Silicon GPUs inside Spooktacular virtual machines.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit":{"kind":"symbol","title":"SpooktacularKit","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit","role":"collection","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","abstract":[{"text":"Create and manage macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/OpenClawGuide":{"title":"Running OpenClaw in Virtual Machines","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawguide","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","abstract":[{"text":"Run two isolated OpenClaw AI agent instances on a single Mac — each with its own workspace, channels, and API keys.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/RemoteDesktop":{"title":"Remote Desktop Access","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/remotedesktop","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","abstract":[{"text":"Connect to Spooktacular VMs via VNC for remote development, QA testing, and design review.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Versioning":{"kind":"article","title":"Versioning & Release Schedule","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/versioning","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Understand what version numbers mean and what to expect from each release."}]},"https://bluebubbles.app":{"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/bluebubbles.app","title":"BlueBubbles","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"BlueBubbles"}],"url":"https:\/\/bluebubbles.app"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GitHubActionsGuide":{"title":"Configuring GitHub Actions Runners","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/githubactionsguide","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","abstract":[{"text":"Run self-hosted macOS GitHub Actions runners in Spooktacular VMs with ephemeral isolation and automatic scaling.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/JenkinsGuide":{"title":"Configuring Jenkins Nodes","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/jenkinsguide","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","abstract":[{"text":"Run Jenkins build agents in Spooktacular VMs for iOS and macOS CI\/CD.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/EC2MacDeployment":{"title":"Deploying on EC2 Mac","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/ec2macdeployment","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","abstract":[{"text":"Run Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac dedicated hosts to double your macOS CI capacity.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/CLIReference":{"kind":"article","title":"Using the spook Command-Line Interface","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/clireference","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines from the terminal with the "},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI."}]}}}